cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.NI, cs.IT 

The paper deals with video streaming, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of heat maps to capture user navigation patterns and the spatiotemporal rate-distortion characteristics of the 360{\deg} video content suggests that the paper may also be relevant to graphics (cs.GR). The optimization problem formulation and the need to efficiently use network bandwidth suggest that the paper may also be relevant to networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT).
